"question": "Design an autocomplete component for millions of users.",
"explanation": "Classic system design question. Topics to cover:\n1. Frontend:\n- Debouncing (300-500ms).\n- Caching (LRU or Map).\n- AbortController to prevent race conditions.\n- Keyboard navigation, accessibility.\n- Virtualization if many results.\n2. API Design:\n- Endpoint: GET /search?q=...&limit=10\n- Response: minimal data (id, label, highlight ranges).\n- Compression: gzip/brotli.\n- HTTP/2 multiplexing.\n3. Backend (high-level):\n- Trie / inverted index in DS terms.\n- Elasticsearch / Algolia in practice.\n- CDN edge cache for popular queries.\n- Personalization layer (user history).\n4. Performance:\n- Prefetch on focus.\n- Predictive loading (top queries).\n- Graceful degradation (if API fails - fallback to local cache).\n5. Analytics:\n- Track query -> click rates.\n- A/B testing for ranking.",
