"explanation": "Problem:\nMove all 0s to the end while maintaining order of non-zero elements.\nDo it in-place.\nExample: [0,1,0,3,12] -> [1,3,12,0,0]\n\nApproach:\nTwo pointers:\n- slow = position to write next non-zero.\n- fast = scans array.\n- When fast finds non-zero, swap with slow position and advance slow.",
"code": "function moveZeroes(nums) {\n  let slow = 0;\n  \n  for (let fast = 0; fast < nums.length; fast++) {\n    if (nums[fast] !== 0) {\n      [nums[slow], nums[fast]] = [nums[fast], nums[slow]];\n      slow++;\n    }\n  }\n}\n \nconst arr = [0, 1, 0, 3, 12];\nmoveZeroes(arr);\n// arr is now [1, 3, 12, 0, 0]"
