"explanation": "Problem:\nGiven meeting time intervals, determine if a person can attend all meetings.\nReturn true if no conflicts.\nExample: [[0,30],[5,10],[15,20]] -> false\nExample: [[7,10],[2,4]] -> true\n\nApproach:\n1. Sort by start time.\n2. Check if any meeting starts before the previous ends.",
"code": "function canAttendMeetings(intervals) {\n  intervals.sort((a, b) => a[0] - b[0]);\n  \n  for (let i = 1; i < intervals.length; i++) {\n    if (intervals[i][0] < intervals[i - 1][1]) {\n      return false; // overlap\n    }\n  }\n  \n  return true;\n}\n \ncanAttendMeetings([[0,30],[5,10],[15,20]]); // false\ncanAttendMeetings([[7,10],[2,4]]);           // true"
